description:
&lt;p&gt;Our Outpatients team in our Wolverhampton Hospital currently have an exciting jobopportunity for the Outpatients Manager role. Join our team and we’ll support you to be your best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are currently in the NHS or a private setting, we’re sure you will find your career with us motivating and rewarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like all of us at Nuffield Health, you do what you do because you care. Every one of our brilliant people is passionate about making a real difference. As an Outpatients manager you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be part of a close-knit team headed by our matron.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With our consultant-led service, you will be working directly with some of the best clinical talent around, gaining experience with new practices, equipment and facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll interact regularly with practitioners from other departments because you understand the importance of continuity in patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To succeed as an Outpatients Manager, you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be organised, highly motivated and engaged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At least 2 years nursing management experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NMC and mentorship qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of outpatients nursing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The outpatient manager will be responsible for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ten outpatients consultation rooms, two treatment rooms and two clinical rooms&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordination and the safe deliveryof minor operation lists&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinating the Nursing workforce to ensure patients receive high quality, compassionate, efficient care whilst in the department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Providingstrong leadership to the outpatient department and also a role model as a senior nurse within the hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want you to be the best you can be. We promise that we will support you with training opportunities, career development options and our unique health &amp; wellbeing focused benefits package. This includes free membership across all of our Fitness &amp; Wellbeing clubs, along with free private healthcare. Not only this, but we also offer a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Sarah Brown (Matron/Head of Clinical Services) on 01902 754177 ext 3202&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - Up to &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£30,000- £45,000 per annum (dependant on experience)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date - 03/12/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - Wolverhampton Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weekly Hours - 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore, please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
